{{Infobox Website | name = ChineseSkill | url = {{URL|http://www.chinese-skill.com/}} | type = [[Privately held company]] | founder = Wang Zhulong | area_served = Worldwide | language = Spanish, English, Japanese, Korean | registration = Free | launch date = August 2014 }}
'''ChineseSkill''' is a free mobile application for learning [[Mandarin Chinese]]. Its course consists of 45 topics which focuses on learning vocabulary and grammar through context and uses a gamification mechanism similar to the language-learning platform [[Duolingo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2 Weird (Free) Learn Chinese Apps that Actually Work!|url=http://startuplivingchina.com/2-weird-free-learn-chinese-apps-actually-work/|website=Startup Living China}}</ref>
ChineseSkill was founded by Wang Zhulong, who noticed a growing trend of people learning Mandarin Chinese while he was stationed in Japan. His partner majored in Chinese language at Peking University.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wangshuo|first1=Luo|title=Learning is just a matter of application|url=http://africa.chinadaily.com.cn/weekly/2015-06/26/content_21108619.htm|agency=China Daily|date=2015-06-26}}</ref>
As of August 2014, ChineseSkill has been available for download on both the [[App Store (iOS)]] and [[Google Play]].
