'''Lizu''' ({{zh|傈苏, 里汝, 吕苏}}; Western Ersu) is a [[Qiangic languages|Qiangic]] language spoken in western [[Sichuan]], China. There are 4,000 speakers according to Sun (1982), and 7,000 speakers according to Chirkova (2008). Muli, where Lizu is spoken, is a multi-ethnic and multi-lingual county, and Lizu has been historically influenced by Mandarin Chinese.<ref>http://elar.soas.ac.uk/deposit/0317</ref>
